00:31:23,006 --> 00:31:24,291
好
Yeah.

191
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:06,338
“土必为你的缘故受咒诅
"Cursed be the ground for our sake.

192
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:13,512
“地必给你长出荆棘和疾黍
"Both thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for us.

193
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:19,635
“因为你本生于土 土归土
"For out of the ground, we were taken. For the dust, we are.

194
00:32:22,023 --> 00:32:24,685
“尘归尘”
"And to the dust, we shall return."

195
00:32:53,430 --> 00:32:54,920
住手！
Stop!

196
00:32:57,434 --> 00:32:58,765
拜托
Please.

197
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,561
瑞德吉！
Redridge!

198
00:33:12,282 --> 00:33:13,567
瑞德吉
Redridge.

199
00:33:27,714 --> 00:33:29,420
你是谁？
And who are you?

200
00:33:30,467 --> 00:33:31,673
无名之辈
Nobody.

201
00:33:33,178 --> 00:33:35,419
我不相信
I doubt that.

202
00:33:35,514 --> 00:33:39,473
你在我酒吧里杀的人 他们才是无名之辈
The men you killed in my bar, now, they were nobody.

203
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:43,135
- 但你却是个大人物 - 他的手没抖
- But you, now. - He ain't got the shakes.

204
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:45,687
- 他不是食人族 - 很好
- He ain't one of them. - Good.

205
00:33:46,483 --> 00:33:50,271
这是一个文明的地方 我们不吃人类
This is a civilized town. We don't eat humans.

206
00:33:51,655 --> 00:33:55,273
大灾难之前的人我们见的不多 现在不是了
We don't see too many people from before. Not anymore.

207
00:33:57,327 --> 00:33:59,989
- 你读书吗？ - 每天
- Do you read? - Every day.

208
00:34:00,330 --> 00:34:03,618
很好，对你好，我也是
All right. Well, good for you. Me, too.

209
00:34:04,584 --> 00:34:05,915
很滑稽
You know, it's funny.

210
00:34:06,002 --> 00:34:10,792
像你我这样老的人，我们是未来
As old as we are, people like you and me, we're the future.

211
00:34:11,675 --> 00:34:12,960
你想从我这得到什么？
What do you want with me?

212
00:34:13,969 --> 00:34:15,459
直奔王题！
Straight to the point!

213
00:34:16,846 --> 00:34:20,259
我喜欢！
I like that!

214
00:34:24,896 --> 00:34:26,682
你不仅仅受过教育
You're not just educated.

215
00:34:28,191 --> 00:34:30,648
我没见过像你这样身手不凡的
I never saw anyone handle themselves the way you did.

216
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:35,399
我不知道你从哪里学到的 但我肯定我能用上你
I don't know where you learned it, but I sure as hell could use it.

217
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:39,403
这个小地方，只是一个开始
This little town, just the beginning.

218
00:34:39,494 --> 00:34:41,576
我准备扩建它
I'm about to expand.

219
00:34:41,663 --> 00:34:43,995
我需要高手的帮助 我需要像你这样的人
I need expert help. I could use someone like you.

220
00:34:44,583 --> 00:34:47,541
谢谢，但我不感兴趣
Thank you, but I'm really not interested.

221
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,953
为我工作的人生活得 比任何行者想像的都好
Well, the people who work for me live better than any walker ever dreamed.

222
00:34:51,047 --> 00:34:53,663
问问瑞德吉，问问这些年轻人，谁都行
Ask Redridge here. Ask the boys, anyone.

223
00:34:54,551 --> 00:34:56,792
真正的床，热乎的饭菜，女人
Real beds, hot food, women.

224
00:34:59,889 --> 00:35:01,504
干净的水
Clean water.

225
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:04,716
你可能会过得更糟，朋友
You could do a lot worse, my friend.

226
00:35:06,229 --> 00:35:07,594
谢谢
Thank you,

227
00:35:09,399 --> 00:35:11,765
但我需要去一个地方
but I got somewhere I need to be.

228
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:13,145
哪里？
Where?

229
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:15,439
西边
West.

230
00:35:15,989 --> 00:35:17,775
西边什么都没有
There is nothing west.

231
00:35:17,866 --> 00:35:19,822
有人告诉我不是这样
I've been told different.

232
00:35:19,909 --> 00:35:21,194
谁？
By who?

233
00:35:26,708 --> 00:35:28,039
告诉你
Tell you what.

234
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:33,041
在这儿过夜，感受一下当地的款待 看看你喜不喜欢
Stay the night. Try a little local hospitality, see how you like it.

235
00:35:33,757 --> 00:35:35,543
我们早上再聊
We'll talk again in the morning.

236
00:35:36,176 --> 00:35:39,168
听我一句，行者，你别无选择
Word of advice, Walker. It's not a choice.

237
00:35:41,514 --> 00:35:43,470
总会有选择
It's always a choice.

238
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:50,637
有人会整晚待在你房外
There'll be someone outside your room all night

239
00:35:50,732 --> 00:35:52,393
如果你需要什么
if you need anything.

240
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:54,065
我不需要任何东西
I don't need anything.

241
00:35:54,736 --> 00:35:56,272
说不准
You never know.

242
00:36:47,580 --> 00:36:51,869
这是给你的 是洗漱的水和一些吃的
This is for you. It's some water for washing and some food.

243
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:55,873
还有点特别的藏品 是这里王人的敬意
Little special reserve, too, compliments of the house.

244
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:04,002
我需要你接着这个或说点什么 这样我才能找到你
I need you to take this or say something so I can find you.

245
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:19,358
- 谢谢 - 不客气
- Thank you. - You're welcome.

246
00:37:19,446 --> 00:37:22,233
- 你还需要点什么吗？ - 不，我很好，谢谢
- Can I get you anything else? - No, I'm fine. Thank you.

247
00:37:22,449 --> 00:37:25,316
你是在战争中失明的 还是因为之后的太阳？
Did you get blinded in the war or by the sun after?

248
00:37:27,996 --> 00:37:30,578
我生来就这样
I was born this way.

249
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:33,532
我想可能是我幸运 因为在它发生的时候
I think probably I'm lucky, because I was already used to being like this

250
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,662
我就已经习惯这样了
by the time it happened.

251
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:38,919
是的，谢谢你的食物
Right, well, thank you for the food.

252
00:37:39,549 --> 00:37:41,039
不客气
You're welcome.

253
00:37:43,303 --> 00:37:45,009
我喜欢你的香水
I like your perfume.

254
00:37:49,726 --> 00:37:51,432
不过是洗发水
It's just shampoo,

255
00:37:52,562 --> 00:37:54,177
但是谢谢
but thank you.

256
00:37:56,816 --> 00:37:58,181
晚安
Good night.

257
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:25,625
我认为他早上是不会改王意的
I don't think he's gonna change his mind by the morning.

258
00:38:26,638 --> 00:38:28,503
他不会留下的
He's not gonna stay.

259
00:38:32,936 --> 00:38:35,052
他跟别人不同
He's different than the others.

260
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:40,103
你不能像使唤别人那样 使唤他
You're not gonna be able to make him do what you want him to do.

261
00:38:41,945 --> 00:38:44,106
谁说我要出马？
Who said anything about me?

262
00:38:46,491 --> 00:38:48,482
我会派索拉娜去
I'll send Solara.

263
00:38:52,539 --> 00:38:54,495
你不能这么做
You can't do that.

264
00:38:54,582 --> 00:38:57,699
是更好地利用她的时候了
It's about time I got better use out of her.

265
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,161
不要
Don't.

266
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:03,413
拜托
Please.

267
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:08,589
求求你，不要 求求你
Please, don't. Please. Please.

268
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:11,925
求求你！
Please!

269
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:25,523
我能进来吗？
Can I come in?

270
00:39:28,074 --> 00:39:29,735
等一下
Give me a minute.

271
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:41,668
已经有人拿来吃的和水
Somebody already came with food and water.

272
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:46,126
我需要的都有了
I got everything I need.

273
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:52,470
你确定吗？
Are you sure about that?

274
00:39:56,102 --> 00:39:58,388
这里真的很亮
It's really bright in here.

275
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:01,224
我是索拉娜
I'm Solara.

276
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:05,059
是的，你刚在楼下装满了我的水壶
Right. You filled my canteen downstairs.

277
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:08,979
是的，你是那个行者，对吗
Yeah. You're the walker, right?

278
00:40:10,033 --> 00:40:11,239
是
Right.

279
00:40:14,454 --> 00:40:18,367
别担心钱 是记在这酒吧的账上的
If you're worried about paying, it's on the house.

280
00:40:18,458 --> 00:40:20,073
付什么钱？
Paying for what?

281
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:24,161
你为什么不坐下来？
Why don't you take a seat?

282
00:40:34,140 --> 00:40:35,255
不
No.

283
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:41,181
不，我不能走，我不能 如果我走了，他会伤害我妈妈
No, I can't go. I can't. If I do, he'll hurt my mom.

284
00:40:42,273 --> 00:40:44,184
- 谁？ - 卡内基
- Who? - Carnegie.

285
00:40:46,319 --> 00:40:47,399
他是你爸爸？
He's your father?

286
00:40:48,196 --> 00:40:51,188
不，但我们都是属于他的
No. No, but we belong to him just the same.

287
00:40:51,282 --> 00:40:54,524
我会睡在地板上
Look, I'll sleep on the floor.

288
00:40:54,702 --> 00:40:56,238
明天告诉他 你过得很愉快
Tomorrow you can tell him you had a good time.

289
00:40:56,329 --> 00:40:59,071
我向你保证我不会惹麻烦的
I promise you I will be no trouble.

290
00:41:02,919 --> 00:41:04,204
求求你？
Please?

291
00:41:11,052 --> 00:41:14,761
马走到象四
Knight to bishop four.

292
00:41:22,814 --> 00:41:24,304
该你了
Your move.

293
00:41:31,239 --> 00:41:33,946
你多大？
So, how old are you?

294
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:36,319
什么？
Excuse me?

295
00:41:36,411 --> 00:41:41,246
我只是以前没见过多少 你这个年龄的人路过这里
It's just that I haven't really seen too many people your age come through here before.

296
00:41:41,332 --> 00:41:43,539
自末日
Well, it's been

297
00:41:47,797 --> 00:41:50,209
已经有30个冬天了
30 winters since the flash.

298
00:41:53,678 --> 00:41:55,293
我真的记不清了
I really don't remember.

299
00:41:56,597 --> 00:42:00,840
你记得那时什么样吗？ 我是说以前的世界
Do you remember what it was like? I mean, in the world before.

300
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:02,175
是的
Yeah.

301
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:07,768
那是什么样子？
Well, what was it like?

302
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:14,312
人们除了必需的，还拥有很多
People had more than they needed.

303
00:42:16,284 --> 00:42:20,618
我们不知道哪些是珍贵的 哪些不是
We had no idea what was precious, what wasn't.

304
00:42:25,626 --> 00:42:29,335
我们扔掉的那些东西 现在人们却要争得你死我活
We threw away things people kill each other for now.

305
00:42:31,632 --> 00:42:33,463
- 真的？ - 是的
- Really? - Yeah.

306
00:42:35,636 --> 00:42:37,092
你有本书
You have a book.

307
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:39,296
- 我可以看一下吗？ - 不，不可以
- Can I see it? - No, you cannot.

308
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:41,597
- 我只是想看看 - 不，我说过不行
- I just, I just wanna look at it. - No. I said no.

309
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:44,300
听着，我甚至不识字！ 拜托，让我看看
Listen, I can't even read! Come on, please, let me just see it.

310
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:48,058
你至于吗？只是本书！
What is with you? lt is just a book!

311
00:42:48,149 --> 00:42:49,889
这不仅仅是一本书
It's not just a book.

312
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:53,059
- 什么意思这不只是一本书？ - 听着
- What do you mean, it's not just a book? - Look.

313
00:42:53,154 --> 00:42:57,648
不要再问有关书的问题了，好吗 不要再问问题，好吧？
No more questions about the book, all right? No more questions. All right?

314
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:25,091
既然你在这儿，我有个问题问你
I got a question for you, since you're here.

315
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:27,935
我或许会回答，或许不
Well, maybe I'll answer it and maybe I won't.

316
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:31,730
你从哪里弄到水？
Where do you get your water?

317
00:43:32,693 --> 00:43:34,058
不能告诉你
Can't tell you that.

318
00:43:34,153 --> 00:43:37,270
- 你不能告诉我还是你不知道？ - 我知道
- You can't tell me or you don't know? - Oh, I know.

319
00:43:38,032 --> 00:43:43,152
但是如果你不告诉我这本书 我就不告诉你水的事
But if you're not talking about the book, I'm not talking about the water.

320
00:43:46,791 --> 00:43:48,827
你真有办法
You're something else, you know.

321
00:43:49,710 --> 00:43:51,621
好吧，我问你另外一个问题
All right, I got another question for you.

322
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:53,327
好
Right.

323
00:43:53,422 --> 00:43:55,629
你饿吗？
You hungry?

324
00:43:55,716 --> 00:43:57,707
这儿有很多吃的
There's a lot of food there,

325
00:43:58,094 --> 00:43:59,834
我吃不了
more than I can eat.

326
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:02,386
告诉你
Tell you what.

327
00:44:02,473 --> 00:44:06,887
我们可以一起分享 就像过去老人那样
We can share it, you know, like old people used to.

328
00:44:09,272 --> 00:44:11,012
好
Okay.

329
00:44:11,107 --> 00:44:12,222
好吗？
Okay?

330
00:44:16,863 --> 00:44:19,570
等等，等下，坐下
Wait a minute, wait a minute. Wait. Sit.

331
00:44:21,909 --> 00:44:22,989
坐下
Sit.

332
00:44:24,787 --> 00:44:26,903
这是给你的
This'll be for you.

333
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:29,075
把手给我
Give me your hands.

334
00:44:31,252 --> 00:44:32,583
你在做什么？
What are you doing?

335
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,911
相信我，把手给我
Trust me. Give me your hands.

336
00:44:39,302 --> 00:44:40,917
闭上你的眼睛
Close your eyes.

337
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:45,842
亲爱的主，感谢你赐给我们食物
Dear Lord, we thank you for this meal.

338
00:44:45,933 --> 00:44:49,391
感谢你赐给我们温暖的床
We thank you for a warm bed

339
00:44:49,478 --> 00:44:53,346
以及在寒冷的夜晚 我们头顶的这顶屋檐
and a roof over our head on cold nights such as this.

340
00:44:54,275 --> 00:44:56,140
这些已经久违了
It's been too long.

341
00:44:56,485 --> 00:44:58,066
这是从你书里来的吗？
Is this from your book?

342
00:44:59,113 --> 00:45:01,775
别打乱，闭上你的眼睛
Don't interrupt. Close your eyes.

343
00:45:03,701 --> 00:45:08,035
我们感谢你在这样艰难的时间里
We thank you for the gift of companionship

344
00:45:08,122 --> 00:45:10,454
赐给我们友谊
in hard times like these.

345
00:45:11,334 --> 00:45:12,699
阿门
Amen.

346
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:18,837
现在可以吃了吗？
Now we eat?

347
00:45:20,092 --> 00:45:21,628
可以了
Now we eat.

348
00:45:52,667 --> 00:45:54,157
早上好，索拉娜
Good morning, Solara.

349
00:45:55,878 --> 00:45:58,665
昨晚如何？你睡得好吗？
How was your night? Did you sleep well?

350
00:45:58,756 --> 00:46:00,417
我按你说的做了
I did like you said.

351
00:46:00,675 --> 00:46:02,916
你当然会按照我说的去做
Of course you did what I said.

352
00:46:04,011 --> 00:46:07,344
但是有用吗？他会留下吗？
But did it work? Is he staying?

353
00:46:08,266 --> 00:46:10,348
我们没聊太多
We didn't do much talking.

354
00:46:11,269 --> 00:46:13,510
索拉娜，亲爱的，吃点东西
Solara, honey, eat something.

355
00:46:17,108 --> 00:46:19,019
妈，把你的手给我
Mom, give me your hand.

356
00:46:21,696 --> 00:46:23,357
闭上你的眼睛
Close your eyes.

357
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:25,526
妈，相信我
Mom, trust me.

358
00:46:32,206 --> 00:46:33,446
亲爱的主
Dear Lord.

359
00:46:35,376 --> 00:46:37,458
我们感谢你赐予的食物
We thank you for our food.

360
00:46:38,796 --> 00:46:40,752
感谢你赐给我母亲
Thank you for my mother.

361
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:46,418
感谢你赐给我们屋顶 以及我们的新朋友
Thank you for the roof over our heads and our new friends.

362
00:46:49,223 --> 00:46:50,463
还有...
And...

363
00:46:56,230 --> 00:46:58,892
我想目前就这么多
Well, I guess that's all for now.

364
00:46:59,567 --> 00:47:00,898
阿门
Amen.

365
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:09,782
这是你要记住的词，阿门
That's the word you're looking for. Amen.

366
00:47:12,204 --> 00:47:13,944
这是结尾
That's how you stop.

367
00:47:20,921 --> 00:47:23,162
你说你们没聊什么
You said you didn't talk much.

368
00:47:25,259 --> 00:47:27,466
那他读了什么没有？
But did he do any reading?

369
00:47:29,764 --> 00:47:32,426
- 我在问你问题 - 比尔，别
- I asked you a question. - Bill, don't.

370
00:47:32,516 --> 00:47:35,098
你，闭上你的嘴
You. Shut your mouth.

371
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:47,023
住手！
Stop!

372
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:49,779
你在伤害你的母亲，索拉娜
You're hurting your mother, Solara.

373
00:47:50,618 --> 00:47:53,906
他说过他每天都阅读的，是吗？
He said he read every day. Did he?

374
00:47:54,955 --> 00:47:56,365
住手！
Stop it!

375
00:47:57,291 --> 00:47:59,373
你妈妈希望你告诉我
Your mother would like you to tell me.

376
00:47:59,460 --> 00:48:00,950
我不知道！
I don't know!

377
00:48:02,004 --> 00:48:03,540
